'''欢乐之火'''（{{lang-en|''Feu de joie''}}，语源自法语“[[篝火|篝火]]”）是源自英国，利用[[步枪|步枪]]营造气氛的喜庆仪式，呈现的方式是由成列的[[仪仗队|步枪队]]对空中连续发出枪响，制造出“啪——哒——哒——”的声效。这种仪式是用在全国欢庆的庆典中，在18－19世纪时，只有在庆贺军事胜利和君主诞辰的场合才会使用。英国最近一次出现这种仪式，是在庆贺[[英女王|英女王]][[伊丽莎白二世|伊丽莎白二世]][[英女王寿辰|80岁诞辰]]和[[伊丽莎白二世登基钻禧纪念|钻禧]]的庆典。<ref>{{cite news|title=Diamond Jubilee: Guide to the weekend of events|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-18147354|newspaper=BBC News|date=30 May 2012|quote=After arriving at Buckingham Palace, the Royal Family will appear on the balcony and watch an RAF flypast. Then, in the forecourt, The Queen's Guard will perform a '''Feu de Joie''' - a cascade of rifle fire interspersed by the National Anthem.|accessdate=2013-12-04|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112012222/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-18147354|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

在英国以外，{{tsl|en|Royal Military College of Canada|加拿大皇家军事学院}}、澳洲{{tsl|en|Royal Military College, Duntroon|邓特伦皇家军事学院}}、[[纽西兰国防军|纽西兰国防军]]和[[新加坡国庆庆典|新加坡国庆庆典]]也有“欢乐之火”的传统和仪式。<ref>{{cite book|author=Edmund Burke|title=Ceremonial Traditions of the Australian Army|pages=37页|url=http://www.24rarassociation.com/customsandtraditions.pdf|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150118163319/http://www.24rarassociation.com/customsandtraditions.pdf|archivedate=2015-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=New Zealand Militia firing a feu de joie during the 1901 royal tour, 1901|url=http://mp.natlib.govt.nz/detail/?id=8669&l=en|publisher=National Library of New Zealand|quote=New Zealand Militia in Auckland firing a '''feu de joie''' during the 1901 royal tour.|access-date=2013-12-04|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304071908/http://mp.natlib.govt.nz/detail/?id=8669&l=en|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=12 things to look forward to at this year’s National Day Parade|url=http://news.xin.msn.com/en/12-things-to-look-forward-to-at-this-year%E2%80%99s-national-day-parade-1?page=39|newspaper=MSN News|date=19 July 2013|quote='''FEU DE JOIE''' by the Guards of Honor continegents.}}{{deadlink}}</ref>

